Good: 

Regulations Considered

1. Legal Enforceability Before Disbursement (Section 2.4)
All credit agreements and security documentation must be legally enforceable prior to disbursement. This includes proper execution of contracts, completion of collateral registration, and documented legal review for complex or high-value exposures.

2. Credit File Completeness (Section 6.3)
Credit files must contain all mandatory assessment, approval, legal, and compliance documentation before disbursement. Incomplete files must not proceed to disbursement without a formally approved exception.

3. Conditions Precedent (Section 6.5)
All approved conditions precedent must be satisfied and verified before funds are released, ensuring that key legal and risk safeguards are in place.

Compliance Report

The institution is fully compliant with the requirements under Sections 2.4, 6.3, and 6.5 for corporate loan disbursement.

In line with Section 2.4, all sampled loan files contained legally enforceable agreements supported by executed contracts, verified collateral registration documents, and documented legal opinions. No disbursements were made before enforceability conditions were met.

As required by Section 6.3, credit files were complete and included risk assessments, approval records, legal documentation, and compliance checks. There were no missing or expired documents in the reviewed samples.

In accordance with Section 6.5, all conditions precedent were verified and signed off before funds were released. Disbursement controls were consistently applied, and no exceptions were observed.

These results demonstrate strong adherence to legal, documentation, and pre-disbursement control requirements, indicating a well-governed corporate lending process.


BAD:

Regulations Considered

1. Legal Enforceability (Section 2.4)
2. Credit File Completeness (Section 6.3)
3. Conditions Precedent (Section 6.5)

Compliance Report

The institution is compliant with Sections 2.4, 6.3, and 6.5.

All required documents were available and the process was followed as per policy.
Disbursement was done after approvals and checks were completed.
No major issues were identified.



